---- MODULE MCDieHarder ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- (**************************************************************************) (* The following definitions duplicate the original *) die hard problem. To have TLC find a solution, we must tell it what values to use for  * ) constant parameters Jug and Capacity but as mentioned in previous comments - configuration file does not allow function-valued expressions so this module extends DieHarder by defining functions MCCapacity(Jug) *) (* which is used instead of original one. Similarly MCGoal (which should be substituted with Goals from specification), that tells TLC to substitute it for  * ) the goal in configuration file and Jug, Capacity are defined using these new constants as well.)
(* ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ CONSTANTS   *) (* The set of all jugs.                                                                                                           -> {1/2}*) MCJug == ({0..9}) /\ Goal <= Cardinality(MCGoals)  \* Choose a random value from the domain for Jug, which is defined as subset in DieHarder module *)
(* The set of all capacities.                                                                                                           -> {1/2}*) MCCapacity == IF MCJug = EmptySet THEN {} ELSE [j\in 0..(Cardinality((MCGoal))-3) | j] \* Choose a random value from the domain for Capacit, which is defined as subset in DieHarder module *)
(* The set of all goals.                                                                                                           -> {1/2}*) MCGolas == ({0..9}) /\ Goal <= Cardinality(MCGoals)  \* Choose a random value from the domain for goal, which is defined as subset in DieHarder module *)
(* ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ SPECIFICATION Spec                                                                                                           -> {1/2}*) (* Initialize state with Initial and transition with Next.                                         (**************************************************************************))(============================================================================= ------------------------------------ THEOREM TypeOK => [](NotSolved) ) ====================================================
TLA+ code specification: Goal == MCGoals *) Specification is the same as in DieHarder module, but we substitute constants with our new ones. INVARIANTS section should be defined according to your invariants and preconditions from original problem statement or based on this extended one (if any).
TLA+ code specification: TypeOK == [](NotSolved) *) This is a placeholder for invariant definition, it's not provided in the question. ------------------------------------ THEOREM Not Solvable => []TypeOk ) ==================================================== The theorem states that if system can be solved (i.,e all invariants hold), then there exists some solution to this specification which we assume as unsolvability for now, i..(this is a placeholder and should provide sufficient conditions under whichthe specifcationisnot solvable).
TLA+ code configuration: CONSTANTS Goal = MCGoals Jug <- MCCapacity Capacity  SPECIFICATION Spec INVARIANTS TypeOK NotSolved. *) This is the TLC config file, it tells tlc to substitute constants with our new ones and use them in specification definition as well for checking invariants under certain conditions (i..e all of these should be defined according your problem statement).
